VALUES
(40, 25, 30, 58, 6, 7, 8, 'unprofitable servant', 'Consequences of Unfruitfulness', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of unproductive actions. The unprofitable servant is cast into darkness, while the earth that bears thorns is rejected and faces burning.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 30, 66, 3, 15, 16, 'there shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth', 'Consequences of Spiritual Indifference', 'This connection highlights the consequences of unfaithfulness in service. Both passages emphasize severe repercussions for those who fail to meet expectations, whether through unprofitability or lukewarmness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 30, 56, 3, 14, 14, 'unprofitable servant', 'Connection of Fruitfulness and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the consequences of being unfruitful. The unprofitable servant faces punishment, while believers are encouraged to maintain good works to avoid being unfruitful.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 30, 65, 1, 13, 13, 'darkness', 'Darkness and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of darkness as a consequence of judgment. The ''outer darkness'' in Matthew and the ''blackness of darkness'' in Jude suggest a similar fate for the unfaithful.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 30, 24, 15, 1, 2, 'cast ye the unprofitable servant', 'Judgment and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment and the consequences of unfaithfulness. Both passages emphasize a separation from God and the resulting fate of those deemed unworthy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 66, 1, 7, 7, 'when the Son of man shall come', 'Connection of Christ''s Return', 'This connection highlights the return of the Son of man in glory, as noted in both passages. Both emphasize the visibility and significance of His coming, with every eye seeing Him and the reaction of the earth''s inhabitants.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 53, 1, 7, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Christ''s Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord Jesus with angels. Matthew speaks of the Son of man coming in glory, while 2 Thessalonians describes Jesus being revealed from heaven with mighty angels.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 40, 19, 28, 28, 'throne of his glory', 'Connection of Thrones and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of the Son of man sitting on the throne of his glory. Matthew 25:31 speaks of this event in the context of judgment, while Matthew 19:28 refers to the promise of the disciples sharing in this authority.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 40, 16, 27, 27, 'Son of man shall come in his glory', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Son of man in glory, accompanied by angels. They also highlight the theme of rewarding individuals according to their works.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 41, 8, 38, 38, 'Son of man shall come in his glory', 'Connection of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Son of man in glory, highlighting the role of the holy angels. This connection underscores the significance of being unashamed of Jesus in the context of His glorious return.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 65, 1, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Christ''s Return', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Lord with his saints. Matthew speaks of the Son of man coming in glory, while Jude references the Lord coming with ten thousands of his saints.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 31, 19, 9, 7, 7, 'throne of his glory', 'Judgment and Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a throne associated with judgment. Matthew speaks of the Son of man sitting on his throne, while Psalms mentions the Lord preparing his throne for judgment.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 39, 3, 18, 18, 'separate them one from another', 'Separation of Righteous and Wicked', 'This connection highlights the theme of discernment between the righteous and the wicked. Both passages emphasize a judgment where individuals are separated based on their faithfulness to God.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 40, 13, 49, 49, 'separate them one from another', 'Separation of Righteous and Wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the separation of people at the end of time, with Matthew 25:32 describing the division of nations like sheep and goats, while Matthew 13:49 speaks of angels severing the wicked from the just. This connection highlights a common theme of judgment and classification.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 47, 5, 10, 10, 'separate them one from another', 'Judgment and Separation', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment, as both passages describe a process of separation based on actions. Matthew 25:32 speaks of separating nations like sheep and goats, while 2 Corinthians 5:10 emphasizes individuals appearing before Christ''s judgment seat for their deeds.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 19, 98, 9, 9, NULL, 'Judgment and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine judgment. Matthew 25:32 speaks of separating nations, while Psalms 98:9 highlights judging the earth with righteousness.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 26, 34, 17, 22, 'he shall separate them one from another', 'Judgment of the Flock', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment among groups, specifically the separation of sheep from goats and the distinction between cattle. This connection highlights the divine authority in discerning between the righteous and the unrighteous.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 19, 96, 13, 13, NULL, 'Judgment and Separation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment, with Matthew 25:32 illustrating the separation of people as a shepherd does with sheep and goats, while Psalms 96:13 speaks of the Lord coming to judge the earth with righteousness. This connection highlights the divine authority in judgment present in both texts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 32, 40, 3, 12, 12, 'separate them one from another', 'Separation of Righteous and Wicked', 'This connection highlights the theme of separation between the righteous and the wicked. Both passages emphasize the act of gathering the good, represented by sheep and wheat, while the bad, represented by goats and chaff, face destruction.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 19, 100, 3, 3, 'sheep', 'Sheep Imagery in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the imagery of sheep in both passages. Matthew 25:33 refers to the sheep as a symbol of the righteous, while Psalms 100:3 identifies God''s people as ''the sheep of his pasture.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 43, 10, 26, 28, 'sheep on his right hand', 'Connection of Sheep Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''sheep'' as a representation of those who follow and are known by the shepherd. In Matthew, the sheep are distinguished from goats, while in John, the sheep hear the shepherd''s voice and are assured of eternal life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 43, 21, 15, 17, 'sheep on his right hand', 'Connection of Sheep Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''sheep'' in relation to care and guidance. In Matthew, the sheep are distinguished as righteous, while in John, Peter is instructed to ''feed my sheep,'' indicating a responsibility towards them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 19, 45, 9, 9, 'right hand', 'Right Hand Symbolism', 'This connection highlights the significance of the ''right hand'' in both passages, where the right hand represents honor and favor. In Matthew, the sheep are placed on the right, indicating approval, while in Psalms, the queen stands at the right hand, symbolizing her esteemed position.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 1, 48, 13, 14, 'right hand', 'Right and Left Hand Symbolism', 'This connection highlights the significance of the right and left hand in both passages. In Matthew, the sheep are placed on the right, while in Genesis, Joseph positions Ephraim and Manasseh in a manner that emphasizes the importance of the right hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 41, 16, 19, 19, 'right hand', 'Sheep and Right Hand Connection', 'This connection highlights the placement of the righteous, represented by sheep on the right hand in Matthew, and the exaltation of Jesus at the right hand of God in Mark. Both passages emphasize the significance of the right hand as a position of favor and authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 33, 44, 2, 34, 35, 'right hand', 'Right Hand Positioning', 'This connection highlights the significance of being positioned at the right hand, as both passages reference the right hand as a place of honor and authority. In Matthew, the sheep are placed on the right, while in Acts, the Lord commands to sit at His right hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 34, 60, 1, 19, 20, 'prepared for you from the foundation of the world', 'Foundation of the World', 'This connection highlights the concept of being prepared ''from the foundation of the world'' in both passages. Matthew speaks of inheriting a kingdom prepared, while 1 Peter refers to Christ being foreordained before the same foundation.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 34, 59, 2, 5, 5, 'inherit the kingdom prepared for you', 'Inheritance of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of inheriting the kingdom. Matthew speaks of those blessed by the King as inheritors, while James highlights the poor as heirs of the kingdom promised to those who love God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 34, 66, 21, 7, 7, 'inherit the kingdom prepared for you', 'Inheritance of the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance in both passages. Matthew speaks of inheriting the kingdom, while Revelation emphasizes inheriting all things.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 34, 66, 13, 8, 8, 'from the foundation of the world', 'Foundation of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of preparation from ''the foundation of the world.'' This highlights the eternal nature of God''s plan for salvation and judgment.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
